---
description: Base frontend rules for Vue + TypeScript project
alwaysApply: true
---

# Philosophy
- Ship > perfect
- Readable > clever
- Consistency > best practice
- Working UI > pixel-perfect UI

# General Coding
- Keep code simple and easy to understand
- Prefer explicit and clear logic over clever solutions
- Avoid unnecessary abstraction
- Avoid premature optimization

# Architecture
- Follow existing project structure
- Do not introduce new patterns unless necessary
- Keep consistency with current codebase

# Constraints
- Do not rewrite entire files
- Do not refactor unrelated code
- Only modify what is necessary
- Keep changes minimal and scoped

# AI Behavior
- Follow existing code style strictly
- Keep solution minimal
- Do not over-engineer
- Prefer incremental improvements

# Anti-Overthinking
- Prefer good enough over perfect
- Stop after delivering a working solution
- Do not attempt to optimize unless required